Package hackerrank

Class BstSearchCloseToZero

  • java.lang.Object
    • hackerrank.BstSearchCloseToZero
  • public class BstSearchCloseToZero
extends java.lang.Object
    Given a Binary Search Tree, return whether it contains any value in the range [-3, 3] (both ends included). Definition: A binary search tree is a binary tree where, for each node, the values in the left subtree are strictly smaller than the node's, and the values in the right subtree are strictly larger than the node's. Constraints:
    • Tree contains between 1 and 10^6 nodes.
    • The tree contains distinct values.
